<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-07-08T20:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-07-08T20:36:00-05:00" n="1003" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1003">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.002/29.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-07-08T19:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1913—7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>315. De la Barra resigned the position of Minister of Foreign Affairs
                            today. The Department should advise me as to my attitude toward the new
                            Minister. I have not yet ascertained the cause of De la Barra’s
                            resignation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>